.TH "get_adapter_status" 9 "get_adapter_status" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_adapter_status \- get adapter status of a slot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" get_adapter_status
.BI "(struct hotplug_slot *hotplug_slot "  ","
.BI "u8 *value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hotplug_slot" 12
slot to get status
.IP "value" 12
pointer to store status
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
ACPI doesn't provide any formal means to access adapter status.
Instead, we fake adapter status from _STA.
